description: Apparently of North Germanic origin, compare Danish alf, Swedish alf, alv, Old Norse alfr (“elf”). Doublet of elf and oaf.

entries.meaning: (obsolete) A changeling or elf child; a child left by fairies.
(obsolete) A deformed or foolish child; a simpleton; an oaf.
examples: Say that the Fayrie left this Aulfe, And tooke away the other.
